{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\nThe scc LOC/size analyzer for the code_health lens: produces the `loc` payload of `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]` from `scc --format json`, fails closed (Unavailable) when scc is unavailable, and never fabricates zeros.\n\n## Approach & rationale (G6/T1/A1 — self-contained, no cross-layer coupling)\n`scc_loc.py` is SELF-CONTAINED: it invokes scc via its own `subprocess` and parses the JSON itself (a trivial, stable read of per-file `Code`+`Location`). It does NOT import from `rebar.grounding` — the `analyzers` package stays independent of the grounding layer (clean layering; avoids a metrics<->grounding dependency). Rationale (A1 ANTI-FP): the scc JSON extraction is ~10 lines of field access, NOT a shared abstraction worth cross-layer coupling; grounding's own `_scc_files` serves a different consumer (Engine-B detectors). If a third consumer ever appears (Rule-of-Three), extraction to a shared module is deferred to then (YAGNI now). New analyzers live in `analyzers/` (NOT the quarantined `adapters/`).\n\n## Concrete contracts (single source of truth — 0734 reads these)\n- ENTRY POINT: `scc_loc.analyze(repo_root, scan_roots=None, *, run=_run_scc) -> AnalyzerResult | Unavailable`. `run` is an injectable runner (default shells `[\"scc\",\"--format\",\"json\", <root>]` via `subprocess.run`) so tests need no live scc.\n- LOC PAYLOAD: `AnalyzerResult.loc = {\"files\": {<relpath:str>: <loc:int>}, \"max_loc\": <int>}`. scc JSON is TWO-LEVEL: `data` is a list of language-group objects, each with a `\"Files\"` array of per-file entries `{\"Code\": int, \"Location\": str}`. The parser flattens BOTH levels (`for group in data: for entry in group.get(\"Files\", []): ...`) — the same flattening grounding's `_scc_files` does; iterating `data` directly would yield nothing. Each `Location` is made repo-relative and POSIX-normalized before use as a key: `files[PurePath(os.path.relpath(entry[\"Location\"], repo_root)).as_posix()] = entry[\"Code\"]`. `max_loc = max(files.values(), default=0)`.\n- `_ACCRUING_SINCE = \"2026-07-01T00:00:00+00:00\"` — a concrete module-level ISO-8601 constant (the metrics-epic accrual date), matching the existing reader-module family.\n- FAIL-CLOSED (returns `Unavailable(reason, _ACCRUING_SINCE)` AND emits `logger.warning(\"scc unavailable: %s\", reason)`): scc binary missing (`FileNotFoundError` from `subprocess`), non-zero exit, empty stdout, or unparseable JSON. A SUCCESSFUL empty result (`[]`, e.g. all-ignored tree) is NOT unavailable -> `AnalyzerResult(loc={\"files\": {}, \"max_loc\": 0})`.\n\n## Grounding (E4 — verified via Read)\n- CONFIRMED scc emits per-file LOC as JSON (`scc --format json`); each file entry has `Code`/`Location` (engine_b_backends.py:376,412 read exactly these, independently).\n- `AnalyzerResult` / `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` from prerequisite `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`; `[metrics]` extra `[rebar:9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed]`; `[code_health]` config `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]` (all depends_on edges recorded). This adapter does NOT use `resolve_analyzer` (it IS an analyzer implementation).\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command; tests use the injectable `run`, no live scc)\n- [ ] parse: `run` returns canned scc JSON for files at 100 & 850 LOC -> `analyze` returns `AnalyzerResult` with `loc[\"files\"]` keyed by repo-relative POSIX paths and `loc[\"max_loc\"] == 850`. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_parse`.\n- [ ] missing binary: `run` raises `FileNotFoundError` -> `Unavailable(reason, _ACCRUING_SINCE)`, no crash, no zeros. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_missing_binary`.\n- [ ] non-zero exit AND unparseable/empty stdout each -> `Unavailable`. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_bad_output`.\n- [ ] successful empty output (`[]`) -> `AnalyzerResult(loc={\"files\":{},\"max_loc\":0})`, not Unavailable. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_empty_tree`.\n- [ ] (supplementary) live scc smoke, skipif scc absent. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_live -m integration`.\n\n## Rollback: revert is a clean delete of the two new files (no existing file is modified).\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 9597, e7a0 (recorded depends_on).\n## Files likely touched\n- src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/__init__.py (new; package marker)\n- src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py (new; self-contained scc invoke + parse -> AnalyzerResult.loc)\n- tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784612449115992001,"uuid":"9eb78aac-0370-4406-ba20-9406a9c9fd30"}